"You horrify me."

I sponged the wound, cleaned it, dressed it, and finally covered it over with cotton wadding and
carbolised bandages. He lay back without wincing, though he bit his lip from time to time.

"How is that?" I asked when I had finished.

"Capital! Between your brandy and your bandage, I feel a new man. I was very weak, but I have had a
good deal to go through."